==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Latin [[crux]].  Cognate with Old High German [[kruzi|krūzi]] (German [[Kreuz]]), Old Saxon [[kruci|krūci]] (Dutch [[kruis]]), Old Irish [[cros]] (Welsh [[croes]], Gaelic [[crois]], Old Norse [[kross]] (English [[cross]])), Old French [[croiz]] (French [[croix]]), Spanish [[cruz]] and many others.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/kru:ʧ/}}

===Noun===
'''crūċ'''
# a [[cross]]

===Descendents===
*Middle English [[crouch]]

